message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "bio-sfm-trust-audit: cost-aware LLM trust-routing over specialist scientific models"
abstract: >-
  An audit of how a general LLM routes trust over a fallible specialist scientific
  model under verification cost (trust / verify / default / defer). Across a
  perturbation dry-run, a single-cell foundation-model cue, and protein-structure
  prediction (Boltz-2 / pLDDT), the robust finding is cautionary: the reasoning
  layer is cue-sensitive; surfacing raw calibrated confidence is the robust lever;
  packaging it as a calibrated reliability interface is not a free win and is
  model-dependent (neutral for Sonnet, harmful for the more risk-averse Opus,
  which over-verifies). See REPORT.md.
